data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_074d84d298cc5bd800699fc3b3c8ec819483d1821b0c876e4e","logprobs":[],"output_index":2,"sequence_number":429,"text":"Foundry Agent Service is Microsoft’s managed runtime in **Microsoft Foundry** for building and operating **AI agents** end-to-end (development → deployment → production). It’s aimed at moving beyond “chatbots” into **automation** that can make decisions, call tools, and run within real business workflows—with governance and operational controls built in.【5:0†source】\n\n### What it does\n- **Runs agents in production**: provides the service layer that connects your agent to models, tools, and frameworks, and manages the agent’s lifecycle in a scalable way.【5:0†source】\n- **Orchestrates tool use**: manages conversations/threads and coordinates when the model should call tools (for data grounding or taking actions).【5:0†source】\n- **Enforces trust & safety / policy**: includes content safety and “production guardrails” so outputs are more governable than a raw LLM integration.【5:0†source】\n- **Integrates with enterprise plumbing**: designed to plug into identity, networking, and observability so you can operate agents like other production services.【5:0†source】\n\n### Tools you can attach to agents\nFoundry Agent Service supports a catalog of **built-in and partner tools** that agents can invoke as needed, including:\n- **Knowledge / grounding tools** (bring in data): Azure AI Search, File Search, Microsoft Fabric, and web grounding (Bing), among others.【5:1†source】\n- **Action tools** (do work): Azure Logic Apps, OpenAPI-based tools, MCP endpoints, function calling, Azure Functions, and browser automation.【5:1†source】\n\n### When you’d use it\nUse Foundry Agent Service when you want an agent that:\n- retrieves grounded information (private or public),\n- takes actions across systems (tickets, workflows, APIs),\n- and must be **secure, observable, and scalable** for production rather than a demo.【5:0†source】【5:1†source】\n\nIf you tell me your scenario (e.g., customer support, invoice processing, internal knowledge assistant) and where your data lives (SharePoint/Fabric/SQL/Azure AI Search/etc.), I can suggest a concrete agent + tool setup."}

